Name: William Goldman
Designation: Hollywood Truth-Teller - Master of Story Structure
Bio: William Goldman (1931-2018), American novelist, playwright, and screenwriter. Won Academy Awards for 'Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid' and 'All the President's Men.' Author of 'The Princess Bride' (both novel and screenplay) and the Hollywood memoir 'Adventures in the Screen Trade,' where he coined the famous phrase 'Nobody knows anything' about what makes a successful film. Known for his cynical wisdom...
